18/03/2009
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Swedish Minister for EU Affairs Cecilia Malmstrom says her country hopes to open "a chapter or two" in Turkey's EU accession talks in the second half of this year, media reported on Tuesday (March 17th).
Sweden takes over the rotating six-month presidency from the Czech Republic on July 1st.
The stumbling block is that Ankara refuses to offer Greek Cypriot planes and ships free access to Turkish airports and ports until the EU fulfils its pledge to ease the isolation of Turkish Cypriots.
Turkey began membership talks in October 2005 but has so far opened only ten of the 35 negotiation chapters.
(Anadolu news agency, Dogan news agency, Hurriyet - 17/03/09)
